div.p: state_evolution IRQ0 fires every 10ms (100Hz PIT) Preemptive, non-cooperative

g.text: PHASE 0 STEADY STATE: Process A Running (Ring 3)
Ready Queue Circular Linked List of PCBs
PHASE 7 IRET: Return to Process B's User Code

div.p: CPU Registers (User Context) CS = 0x1B (user code, RPL=3) SS = 0x23 (user data, RPL=3) EIP = 0x00401234 (user code addr) ESP = 0xBFFFFE80 (user stack) EFLAGS.IF = 1 (interrupts enabled) CR3 = proc_a.page_directory (phys)
Divisor Calculation 1,193,182 Hz divisor = 100 Hz divisor = 11,932 Counter decrements each input tick. At zero output line asserts.
PIC Arbitration IRQ0 asserts on PIC pin IRQ0 not masked asserts INTR CPU acknowledges INTA cycle PIC responds: vector = 32 (0x20) (Master remapped: IRQ0 vec 32)
TSS.ESP0 = proc_a.kernel_stack_top (updated last context switch) SS0 = 0x10 (kernel data segment)
Kernel Stack after CPU push (topbottom): [esp+0 ] SS_user = 0x23 [esp+4 ] ESP_user = 0xBFFFFE80 [esp+8 ] EFLAGS = 0x00000202 (IF=1) [esp+12] CS_user = 0x1B [esp+16] EIP_user = 0x00401234 return addr
IDT Gate Descriptor [32] offset_low = isr_32 & 0xFFFF selector = 0x08 (kernel code) flags = 0x8E (interrupt gate, DPL=0) IF cleared on entry (no re-entrant IRQ)

add esp, 4 ; pop frame ptr arg

Round-Robin Policy next = current_process->next Walk circular list skipping BLOCKED / DEAD processes. If next == current no switch.
mov cr3, proc_b.page_directory TLB fully flushed all user-space translations evicted. Kernel PDEs (idx 768-1023) shared no re-walk needed.

Why this MUST happen here: Next interrupt while B runs CPU reads TSS. If ESP0 still = A's stack CPU pushes frame onto A's stack. A's state silently corrupted. Crash later, not now. tss_set_kernel_stack(proc_b->kernel_stack_top) kernel_tss.esp0 = 0xC0203FFF

p.strong: Process B's kernel stack (as of last preemption):

div.p: ret back into isr_common_stub pop gs; pop fs; pop es; pop ds (restore B's seg regs) popa restore B's EAX,ECX,EDX,EBX,EBP,ESI,EDI add esp, 8 remove int_no + err_code iretd 5-field restore (ring-change variant): pops EIP B's user code address pops CS 0x1B (ring 3) pops EFLAGS 0x00000202 (IF=1) pops ESP B's user stack pointer pops SS 0x23 (user data)

The Illusion Maintained: Process B resumes at its exact instruction. Its registers are identical to when it was preempted. It has no knowledge that A ran or that the timer fired. 10ms later: IRQ0 fires again cycle repeats.
